{"type":"message","id":"27c07cb0","parentId":"a7333760","timestamp":"2026-04-05T06:10:01.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_pnQYrA1zgIeoZlePvU9XVM","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":1800,"label":"ultraplan-magi-redesign","task":"# ULTRAPLAN: Complete MAGI Web App Redesign — Zero Bug Tolerance\n\nYou have up to 30 minutes to think deeply about this task. Do NOT execute anything.\nYour job is to produce a comprehensive, actionable plan that another team of 4 agents will execute.\n\n## Task\nLucy wants to completely redesign/overhaul the MAGI web application to be significantly better. The redesign must be so thorough that Lucy encounters ZERO bugs when using it. Every edge case, every mobile interaction, every API failure state must be handled.\n\n## What is MAGI?\nMAGI is a custom-built web dashboard for managing a Council of 12 AI agents. It runs on a DigitalOcean VPS (8GB RAM, 4vCPU). Stack: vanilla HTML/CSS/JS frontend (no React/build tools), Fastify backend, WebSocket for real-time chat.\n\n## Current Architecture\n\n### Frontend (~/magi-v2/frontend/) — 18 pages, all vanilla HTML\nEach page is a self-contained HTML file with inline CSS/JS. No shared component system.\n\nPages by size (lines):\n- settings: 970 lines\n- chat: 847 lines (WebSocket-based, real-time)\n- roundtable: 708 lines\n- leads: 668 lines\n- vault: 560 lines\n- icat: 494 lines\n- analytics: 412 lines\n- knowledge: 404 lines\n- tasks: 354 lines\n- mission: 343 lines\n- monitor: 341 lines\n- files: 334 lines\n- dashboard: 241 lines (main landing/app launcher)\n- pipeline: 160 lines\n- broadcast: 135 lines\n- reports: 120 lines\n- notifications: 83 lines\n- login: 71 lines\n\nShared assets: marked.min.js, highlight.min.js, atom-one-dark.min.css, Inter font woff2 files\n\n### Backend (~/magi-v2/backend/server.js) — 2,273 lines\nFastify + WebSocket. Key API groups:\n- /api/auth/* — login, logout, session\n- /api/sessions/* — chat sessions CRUD + messaging\n- /api/agents — agent listing\n- /api/vault/* — notes, graph, search (Obsidian-like)\n- /api/files/* — VPS file manager\n- /api/analytics/* — usage stats, daily, events\n- /api/monitor/* — agent status, routing, memory\n- /api/tasks/* — kanban board\n- /api/leads/* — 158K business leads, map, export\n- /api/icat/* — contacts, templates, auto-rules\n- /api/knowledge-base/* — research archive\n- /api/roundtable/* — multi-agent discussions\n- /api/notifications — alerts\n- /api/whatsapp/send — messaging\n- /ws/chat — WebSocket for real-time\n\n### Legacy Backend (~/council-room/backend/server.js) — 6,409 lines\nOriginal council-room with Telegram bot, agent souls, cron jobs. Still runs alongside MAGI v2.\nSeparate pages served by Caddy: it-support, admin, voice-call, pixel-office, etc.\n\n### Infrastructure\n- Caddy reverse proxy (magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io)\n- PM2 process management\n- CouchDB for Obsidian LiveSync\n- Docker for some services\n- All on single VPS\n\n### Current Design System\n- Dark theme throughout\n- CSS vars: --bg:#060a14, --primary:#34d399, --accent:#6366f1\n- Glass morphism effects (backdrop-filter, subtle borders)\n- Inter font family\n- Lucide icons\n- JetBrains Mono for code\n- Responsive but inconsistent across pages\n\n### Dashboard (Landing)\nApp launcher pattern — grid of cards linking to each sub-app. Gradient MAGI logo, status pill, Lucide icons.\n\n### Chat (Most Complex Page — 847 lines)\nWebSocket real-time chat. Features: sidebar with sessions, markdown rendering, code highlighting, agent picker, typing indicators, session management. CSS vars differ slightly from dashboard.\n\n## Known Issues / Pain Points\n1. No shared component system — every page reimplements common UI (nav, sidebar, cards, modals)\n2. CSS variables inconsistent between pages (some use --bg:#0a0e1a, some --bg:#060a14)\n3. No global navigation — each page is isolated, you navigate via dashboard\n4. Mobile experience varies per page\n5. No dark/light mode toggle (all dark)\n6. No loading states for many API calls\n7. Error handling inconsistent — some pages show toast, some show nothing\n8. No offline/reconnect handling for WebSocket\n9. Code duplication — auth check, API calls, toast, markdown rendering duplicated everywhere\n10. Some pages are stubs (notifications: 83 lines, login: 71 lines)\n\n## Your Output Must Include\n\n### 1. Problem Analysis\n- What exactly needs fixing (categorized: UX, DX, performance, reliability, visual)\n- Current state assessment per page\n- Critical bugs/gaps that WILL cause issues\n- What's actually working well (keep these)\n\n### 2. Architecture Decision: Shared Component System\nShould we:\nA) Keep vanilla HTML but extract shared CSS/JS into importable modules\nB) Adopt a micro-framework (Alpine.js, Petite-Vue, Lit)\nC) Full React/Vue/Svelte rewrite\nD) Something else\n\nEvaluate each with pros/cons/effort. Must stay deployable on this VPS with no build pipeline.\n\n### 3. Design System Specification\n- Unified CSS variable set (one source of truth)\n- Typography scale\n- Spacing system\n- Color palette (primary, accent, semantic colors)\n- Component library (buttons, cards, inputs, modals, toasts, tables, badges)\n- Animation/transition standards\n- Responsive breakpoints\n- Dark mode tokens (extensible to light mode later)\n\n### 4. Shared Infrastructure\n- Global navigation (sidebar? top bar? both?)\n- Authentication wrapper\n- API client (fetch wrapper with auth, error handling, retry)\n- WebSocket manager (reconnect, heartbeat)\n- Toast/notification system\n- Loading states\n- Error boundaries\n- Markdown renderer (shared instance)\n- Code highlighting (shared)\n\n### 5. Page-by-Page Redesign Plan\nFor EACH of the 18 pages:\n- Current state (what works, what's broken)\n- Proposed changes\n- Priority (P0 = critical, P1 = important, P2 = nice-to-have)\n- Estimated effort (hours)\n- Dependencies on shared infrastructure\n- Edge cases to handle\n- Mobile-specific considerations\n\n### 6. Bug Prevention Checklist\nFor EVERY page, verify:\n- [ ] Loading states for ALL async operations\n- [ ] Error states for ALL API calls (network error, 401, 500)\n- [ ] Empty states (no data, first use)\n- [ ] Mobile responsive (320px to 1920px)\n- [ ] Touch targets ≥ 44px on mobile\n- [ ] Keyboard navigation works\n- [ ] WebSocket reconnection (if applicable)\n- [ ] Auth redirect on 401\n- [ ] Input validation\n- [ ] XSS prevention (HTML escaping)\n- [ ] Memory leaks (intervals, event listeners cleaned up)\n- [ ] Back button works correctly\n- [ ] Scroll position preserved where expected\n- [ ] Copy/paste works for code blocks\n- [ ] Long text truncation with tooltip\n\n### 7. Execution Plan (4 Parallel Agents)\nBreak the work into 4 parallel streams that can be executed by 4 sub-agents simultaneously:\n- Agent 1: ???\n- Agent 2: ???\n- Agent 3: ???\n- Agent 4: ???\n\nDefine clear boundaries so agents don't conflict (no two agents editing the same file simultaneously).\nDefine the ORDER of execution (what must be done first, what can be parallel).\n\n### 8. Risk Mitigation\n- What could go wrong during redesign?\n- How to test each page after changes?\n- Rollback plan if something breaks?\n- How to avoid breaking the backend?\n\n### 9. Open Questions\n- What needs Lucy's input before execution?\n- Design preferences not yet known?\n- Feature additions vs pure redesign?\n\n## Rules\n- DO NOT execute any code or make any changes\n- DO NOT use tools that modify files (write, edit, exec)\n- You MAY use read, web_search, web_fetch to gather information\n- Focus on THINKING, not DOING\n- Be thorough — this plan will be executed by 4 agents simultaneously\n- State assumptions explicitly\n- ZERO BUG TOLERANCE — think through every edge case\n- Consider this VPS has 8GB RAM — no heavy build tools\n\n## Context Files to Read\nRead these files to understand the current state:\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/dashboard/index.html (landing page pattern)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/chat/index.html (most complex page)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/settings/index.html (largest page)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/roundtable/index.html (multi-agent feature)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/vault/index.html (Obsidian-like notes)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/login/index.html (auth flow)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/monitor/index.html (agent status)\n- ~/magi-v2/backend/server.js (full backend)\n- /etc/caddy/Caddyfile (routing)\n\nRead as many as you can within your time budget. The more context, the better the plan."}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":2424,"cacheRead":115509,"cacheWrite":109,"totalTokens":118043,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0606,"cacheRead":0.0577545,"cacheWrite":0.00068125,"total":0.11904075}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775369341380}}
