{"type":"message","id":"62bcb0a7","parentId":"65cedf74","timestamp":"2026-04-05T08:57:12.899Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me also read the AlphaClaw theme.css and their CSS patterns — already fetched earlier. I have everything needed. Launching ULTRAPLAN:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_gKGg5AdGFRRU22xChrelvD","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"ultraplan-apex-redesign","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":1800,"task":"# ULTRAPLAN: Complete Visual Redesign — AlphaClaw Apex Style\n\nYou have up to 20 minutes to think deeply. Do NOT execute anything. Produce a comprehensive, actionable plan.\n\n## Task\nRedesign ALL web applications on this server to match AlphaClaw Apex's UI/UX design language. This includes page transition animations, component styling, typography, and interaction patterns. The goal is to make every app feel like a unified, premium product.\n\n## AlphaClaw Apex Design Language (from video analysis)\n\n### Visual DNA\n1. **Monospace-first typography** — JetBrains Mono for ALL text (headings, body, labels, code). Not just code blocks.\n2. **Cyan accent color (#63ebff / #00efff)** — primary interactive color. NOT indigo.\n3. **Background: #0d121b** with subtle grid texture overlay (48px grid lines at ~2.4% white opacity) — NOT gradient orbs\n4. **Sidebar background: #0f141f**, content area: #0f1521\n5. **Border color: rgba(255,255,255,0.06)** default, stronger on hover\n6. **Text hierarchy: primary #c9d1d9, muted #6e7681, dim #424854**\n\n### Page Transition Animation (CRITICAL — this is the hero feature)\nBetween every page/section switch:\n1. Current content fades out (200ms)\n2. Full-screen dark overlay appears\n3. Large centered icon (section emoji) fades in + slight scale-up from 0.8→1.0\n4. Section name text fades in below icon (0.5s after icon)\n5. Hold for ~1 second\n6. Icon + text fade out\n7. New page content fades in from bottom (translateY(20px) → 0) with stagger on child elements\n\nImplementation: This should be a shared JS module (transitions.js) that wraps all navigation. When clicking a nav item:\n```\nnavTo('/chat/', '💬', 'Council Chat')\n```\n\n### Component Patterns\n- **Cards:** Very minimal — just `border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06)`, background slightly elevated, `border-radius: 10px`. No glass-morphism blur.\n- **Buttons:** Cyan gradient button (primary), secondary = subtle border + bg, danger = red tint. All have 1px border.\n- **Sidebar:** Left sidebar with grouped sections. Active item has **cyan left border (3px)** + slightly brighter background. Hover state is subtle bg change.\n- **Stat cards:** Large monospace numbers, small uppercase labels below. Minimal decoration.\n- **Toggle switches:** Cyan when on, pill-shaped, smooth transition.\n- **Tables:** Minimal, no zebra stripes, subtle row border-bottom only.\n- **Inputs:** Dark background (rgba(0,0,0,0.3)), border on focus brightens.\n- **Badges/Pills:** Small, rounded, colored background matching status.\n\n### Micro-animations\n- Cards fade-in with stagger (each card delayed 50ms after previous)\n- Numbers have count-up animation on initial load\n- Sidebar items have smooth 150ms hover transition\n- Loading states use a subtle pulse animation (not spinner)\n- Toast notifications slide up from bottom-right\n\n### Embedded Terminal\n- Monospace, dark background (#0a0e14)\n- Green text for success, red for errors, cyan for info\n- Scrollable with thin scrollbar\n\n### Color Tokens (from AlphaClaw theme.css)\n```css\n--bg: #0d121b;\n--bg-sidebar: #0f141f;\n--bg-content: #0f1521;\n--bg-hover: rgba(99, 235, 255, 0.05);\n--bg-active: rgba(99, 235, 255, 0.08);\n--border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);\n--border-strong: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.11);\n--text: #c9d1d9;\n--text-muted: #6e7681;\n--text-dim: #424854;\n--text-bright: #f3f4f6;\n--accent: #63ebff;\n--accent-dim: rgba(99, 235, 255, 0.4);\n--orange: #d98a58;\n--keyword: #ff7b72;\n--string: #a5d6ff;\n--number: #79c0ff;\n--status-error: #fca5a5;\n--status-warning: #fde047;\n--status-success: #86efac;\n--status-info: #a5f3fc;\n```\n\n## ALL Apps to Redesign\n\n### Tier 1: MAGI v2 (18 pages) — ~/magi-v2/frontend/\nAlready migrated to shared infrastructure. Now need visual redesign.\nPages: dashboard, login, chat, roundtable, vault, knowledge, mission, monitor, analytics, tasks, files, leads, icat, pipeline, broadcast, notifications, reports, settings\n\n### Tier 2: Council Room Legacy (active pages) — ~/council-room/frontend/\n- it-support.html (808 lines) — emergency controls, agent models, Uriel chat, quick commands\n- voice-call/index.html — WebSocket voice call with agents\n- admin.html — admin dashboard\n\n### Tier 3: Paul Simulator (D&D App) — ~/dnd-app/frontend/\n- index.html (1815 lines) — main D&D companion (character sheets, dice, initiative, spells)\n- guide.html (1009 lines) — D&D guide\n- flow.html (322 lines) — flow view\n\n## Your Output Must Include\n\n### 1. Shared Design System Update\nExact CSS to replace the current ~/magi-v2/frontend/shared/core.css with AlphaClaw Apex tokens:\n- New color scheme (cyan accent, grid texture, monospace typography)\n- New background treatment (grid texture, NOT orbs)\n- Updated component styles\n- Transition animation system\n\n### 2. Page Transition Module Spec\n`/shared/transitions.js` — detailed spec for the page transition animation system:\n- How it intercepts navigation\n- The animation sequence (timing, easing, elements)\n- Icon/label config per page\n- How it integrates with existing nav.js\n- Fallback for direct URL access (no transition, just fade-in)\n\n### 3. Navigation Update\nUpdate nav.js spec to match Apex sidebar:\n- Grouped sections with small uppercase headers\n- Active item = cyan left border + brighter bg\n- Monospace font\n- Collapse/expand behavior\n\n### 4. Component Migration Guide\nFor each component type, show exact CSS change from current → Apex style:\n- Cards (glass → minimal border)\n- Buttons (indigo → cyan)\n- Inputs/selects\n- Badges/tags\n- Modals\n- Toast\n- Tables\n- Stat cards with count-up\n\n### 5. Staggered Entry Animation Spec\nHow cards/items animate in on page load:\n- CSS @keyframes\n- JS to add stagger classes\n- Timing (50ms per item)\n\n### 6. Page-by-Page Visual Changes\nFor EACH of the ~25 active pages across all 3 tiers:\n- Current look → Apex look (what changes)\n- Specific color/font/layout changes\n- Animation additions\n- Priority (P0/P1/P2)\n\n### 7. Paul Simulator (D&D) Specific Plan\nThe D&D app has its own aesthetic (fantasy/medieval). Plan for:\n- Keep D&D flavor but adopt Apex's technical polish\n- Dark theme aligned with Apex\n- Monospace for game stats, but serif/display for flavor text?\n- Dice roll animations\n- Character sheet layout improvements\n\n### 8. Execution Plan (4 Agents)\nSplit into 4 parallel work streams:\n- Agent 1: Shared infrastructure update (core.css, components.css, transitions.js, nav.js update)\n- Agent 2: MAGI core pages visual update\n- Agent 3: MAGI ops + business pages visual update\n- Agent 4: Council Room legacy + DnD app visual update\n\n### 9. Count-Up Animation for Stats\nSpec for animated number counting:\n- Start from 0, count up to target\n- Duration proportional to number size\n- Use requestAnimationFrame\n- Easing function (ease-out)\n- Trigger on scroll-into-view (IntersectionObserver)\n\n### 10. Quality Checklist\n- [ ] Every page uses JetBrains Mono\n- [ ] Every page has grid texture background (not orbs)\n- [ ] Cyan (#63ebff) is the accent everywhere\n- [ ] Page transitions work between all nav items\n- [ ] Cards have staggered entrance animation\n- [ ] Stats have count-up animation\n- [ ] Sidebar has cyan left-border active state\n- [ ] All buttons use cyan gradient\n- [ ] All inputs have dark bg + border-focus\n- [ ] Mobile responsive maintained\n- [ ] No visual regression on functionality\n\n## Rules\n- DO NOT execute any code\n- You MAY use read to examine current files\n- Focus on THINKING and SPECIFYING\n- Be extremely precise about CSS values, timing, and animation sequences\n- The plan must be detailed enough for 4 agents to execute without ambiguity\n- Reference the AlphaClaw theme.css tokens throughout"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":2411,"cacheRead":173373,"cacheWrite":525,"totalTokens":176310,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.060275,"cacheRead":0.0866865,"cacheWrite":0.0032812500000000003,"total":0.15024775}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775379369059}}
