{"type":"message","id":"2f271cf4","parentId":"c117241f","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:17:11.263Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_vk3VHV8fzR1vcN9oqVEiT9","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"apex-agent2-landing-core","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# APEX Redesign — Agent 2: Landing Page Overhaul + Core Pages\n\n## CRITICAL: Landing Page Complete Redesign\n\nThe Dashboard at ~/magi-v2/frontend/dashboard/index.html is the LANDING PAGE. Lucy wants a COMPLETE overhaul — not just color swap, but a new layout inspired by AlphaClaw Apex.\n\n### New Landing Page Design:\n\n**Layout:**\n- Full sidebar nav on left (from shared nav.js — `renderNav('dashboard')`)\n- Main content area: NOT just a list of app cards anymore\n\n**Hero Section (top of main content):**\n- Large \"MAGI\" text in JetBrains Mono, font-weight 700, 48px\n- Below: status line showing \"X agents online · System healthy\" with green pulse dot\n- Subtle grid texture background (from core.css)\n\n**Quick Stats Row (below hero):**\n- 4 stat cards in a row: Active Agents, Messages Today, Uptime, Token Usage\n- Each stat card: large monospace number with count-up animation, small uppercase label\n- Cards have `background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border);`\n- Numbers use `data-countup` attribute for animation\n\n**Recent Activity Feed (main area):**\n- Real-time scrolling list of recent events (from /api/analytics/events)\n- Each row: timestamp (dim) | agent name (cyan) | action | detail\n- Minimal table style, no borders except subtle row separator\n\n**Quick Actions Grid (below stats):**\n- 2x3 grid of quick action cards (most used features)\n- Each card: icon + label + subtle description\n- Cards: Chat, Roundtable, Vault, Tasks, Monitor, Settings\n- Hover: border-color brightens, subtle cyan glow\n- Click: triggers page transition animation\n\n**System Health Bar (bottom):**\n- Thin bar showing CPU, Memory, Disk as small progress indicators\n- Green/yellow/red based on thresholds\n\n### Current file reference:\nRead ~/magi-v2/frontend/dashboard/index.html for the current structure.\n\n### Implementation:\n- Import shared core.css, components.css, nav.js, transitions.js, countup.js\n- Use `initTransitions()` on load\n- Quick action cards use `navTo()` for transitions\n- Stats use `data-countup` for number animation\n- Fetch stats from: `/api/agents`, `/api/analytics`, `/api/monitor/agents`\n- Keep the PWA manifest + service worker references\n\n## Core Pages (Visual Update Only)\n\nFor these 4 pages, the shared infrastructure change (core.css) will automatically update most visuals. But check each and fix any remaining inline styles that conflict with Apex:\n\n### Chat (~/magi-v2/frontend/chat/index.html)\n- Read the file\n- Remove any remaining inline CSS that overrides shared tokens\n- Make sure sidebar uses Apex styling (cyan active border, JetBrains Mono)\n- Agent colors in chat can stay unique per agent\n- Welcome screen cards should use stagger-item class\n- Verify it imports transitions.js and uses initTransitions()\n- Add `<script type=\"module\">import { initTransitions } from '/shared/transitions.js'; initTransitions();</script>`\n\n### Vault (~/magi-v2/frontend/vault/index.html)\n- Same: remove conflicting inline CSS\n- Editor area should use JetBrains Mono (already monospace)\n- Note list should have stagger-item class\n- Graph view colors: nodes should be cyan instead of indigo\n\n### Roundtable (~/magi-v2/frontend/roundtable/index.html)\n- Agent response cards: add stagger-item class\n- Remove inline CSS overrides\n- Synthesis section: cyan accent\n\n### Knowledge (~/magi-v2/frontend/knowledge/index.html)\n- Article list: stagger-item class\n- Category badges: use new badge colors\n- Remove inline CSS overrides\n\n## Rules\n- Read EACH file fully before editing\n- Read the NEW shared files (core.css, components.css, nav.js, transitions.js, countup.js) — they may not exist yet, so check and use the spec from the task description above\n- Landing page should feel PREMIUM — this is the first thing Lucy sees\n- Add `class=\"stagger-item\"` to repeating card/row elements\n- Add `data-countup=\"VALUE\"` to stat numbers\n- Import and call `initTransitions()` on every page\n- Ensure nav sidebar appears on all pages\n- Mobile responsive: stats stack to 2x2, quick actions stack to 1 column"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":1206,"cacheRead":182485,"cacheWrite":4241,"totalTokens":187933,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.03015,"cacheRead":0.09124249999999999,"cacheWrite":0.026506250000000002,"total":0.14790375}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775380595126}}
