{"type":"message","id":"720be4bf","parentId":"891315ca","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:17:45.164Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_JJQ3fj61R7CsJbUKYihWDm","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"apex-agent3-ops-biz","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# APEX Redesign — Agent 3: Operations + Business Pages Visual Update\n\nUpdate 14 MAGI pages to Apex visual style. The shared core.css is being updated separately (Agent 1), so your job is to:\n1. Remove any remaining INLINE CSS that conflicts with new Apex tokens\n2. Add stagger-item classes to repeating elements\n3. Add data-countup to stat numbers\n4. Import and init transitions.js\n5. Ensure nav sidebar works on each page\n6. Fix any hardcoded colors (indigo → cyan, old bg values)\n\n## Pages to Update\n\nRead EACH file, then make targeted edits:\n\n### Operations (6 pages):\n1. **settings** (~/magi-v2/frontend/settings/index.html) — Remove inline color overrides. Tab buttons should use cyan active state.\n2. **monitor** (~/magi-v2/frontend/monitor/index.html) — Agent cards: add stagger-item. Stats: add data-countup. Status indicators: use new status colors.\n3. **analytics** (~/magi-v2/frontend/analytics/index.html) — Chart colors: update to cyan/accent palette. Stats: data-countup. Cards: stagger-item.\n4. **tasks** (~/magi-v2/frontend/tasks/index.html) — Kanban columns: use new border. Task cards: stagger-item within columns.\n5. **files** (~/magi-v2/frontend/files/index.html) — File list rows: stagger-item. Breadcrumbs: use new text colors. Disk gauge: cyan fill.\n6. **mission** (~/magi-v2/frontend/mission/index.html) — Overview cards: stagger-item + data-countup. Status indicators: new colors.\n\n### Business (6 pages):\n7. **leads** (~/magi-v2/frontend/leads/index.html) — Lead cards: stagger-item. Map markers: keep as-is. Filters: use new input styles. Stats: data-countup.\n8. **icat** (~/magi-v2/frontend/icat/index.html) — Contact list: stagger-item. Tab system: cyan active.\n9. **pipeline** (~/magi-v2/frontend/pipeline/index.html) — Pipeline stages: use cyan highlights. Deal cards: stagger-item.\n10. **broadcast** (~/magi-v2/frontend/broadcast/index.html) — Update button colors. Template cards: stagger-item.\n\n### System (4 pages):\n11. **notifications** (~/magi-v2/frontend/notifications/index.html) — Notification rows: stagger-item. Unread indicator: cyan.\n12. **reports** (~/magi-v2/frontend/reports/index.html) — Report cards: stagger-item. Charts: cyan palette.\n13. **login** (~/magi-v2/frontend/login/index.html) — MAGI logo: keep gradient but adjust. Login button: cyan primary. Background: grid texture. NO sidebar nav.\n14. **settings** — already listed above\n\n### For EACH page, add this import block if not present:\n```html\n<script type=\"module\">\nimport { initTransitions } from '/shared/transitions.js';\ninitTransitions();\n</script>\n```\nThis can be added to the existing module script block.\n\n### Common inline CSS to FIND AND REMOVE:\nLook for any of these patterns in `<style>` blocks and REMOVE them (they're now in core.css):\n- `:root { ... }` variable definitions\n- `body { background:...; color:...; font-family:... }`\n- `body::before` / `body::after` (background orbs)\n- `::selection { ... }`\n- `::-webkit-scrollbar` rules\n- `@keyframes fadeIn / slideUp / pulse / spin`\n- `*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing:... }`\n\nBut KEEP page-specific styles (layout grids, custom components unique to that page).\n\n### Color replacements to make in remaining inline CSS:\n- `#818cf8` or `#6366f1` (indigo) → `var(--accent)` or `#63ebff`\n- `rgba(99,102,241,...)` (indigo rgba) → equivalent `rgba(99,235,255,...)`\n- `#34d399` (green accent) → `var(--color-success)` (keep green for success only)\n- `--bg:#060a14` or `--bg:#0a0e1a` → remove (use core.css)\n- `font-family:'Inter'` → remove (use core.css JetBrains Mono)\n\n## Rules\n- Read each file BEFORE editing\n- Do NOT rewrite entire files — make TARGETED edits only\n- Keep all functionality intact\n- If a page has its own `<style>` block, trim it to only page-specific styles\n- Add transitions import + initTransitions() call to each page\n- Add stagger-item class to lists of cards/rows (agent grids, file lists, notification rows, etc.)\n- Add data-countup=\"VALUE\" to stat numbers where the JS populates them\n- Login page: NO nav, NO transitions, just visual color update"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":1368,"cacheRead":186726,"cacheWrite":1405,"totalTokens":189500,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0342,"cacheRead":0.093363,"cacheWrite":0.00878125,"total":0.13634925}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775380632028}}
