{"type":"message","id":"0659bc84","parentId":"0518dbcf","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:18:23.473Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_MrIftKdAXxepdofUdYQd6A","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"apex-agent4-legacy-dnd","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# APEX Redesign — Agent 4: Council Room Legacy + Paul Simulator (D&D)\n\nUpdate non-MAGI web apps to Apex design language. These are STANDALONE pages (not using /shared/ modules), so you need to update inline CSS directly.\n\n## Council Room Legacy Pages\n\n### 1. IT Support (~/council-room/frontend/it-support.html — 808 lines)\nThis is a full standalone page with inline CSS/JS. Apply Apex visual overhaul:\n\n**CSS changes:**\n- Replace ALL `:root` variables with Apex tokens:\n  - `--bg:#07080f` → `--bg:#0d121b`\n  - `--s1:#0d0f1a` → `--s1:#0f141f`\n  - `--s2:#111320` → `--s2:#0f1521`\n  - `--indigo:#6366f1` → `--accent:#63ebff` (rename all indigo refs to accent)\n  - `--ivory:#c9d8e8` → `--text:#c9d1d9`\n  - `--ash:#7a9ab8` → `--text-muted:#6e7681`\n- `body { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 13px; }`\n- Replace gradient orb body::before with grid texture:\n  ```css\n  body::before { content:''; position:fixed; inset:0; pointer-events:none; z-index:0;\n    background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,.024) 1px, transparent 1px),\n    linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,.024) 1px, transparent 1px);\n    background-size: 48px 48px; }\n  ```\n- All `rgba(99,102,241,...)` → `rgba(99,235,255,...)`\n- Button hover glows: cyan not indigo\n- Scrollbar: cyan thumb\n- Selection: cyan bg\n\n**Add sidebar navigation** (inline, since this page doesn't use /shared/):\nBuild a minimal left sidebar directly in the HTML with links to:\n- MAGI Dashboard (/)\n- IT Support (current, active)\n- Voice Call (/voice-call/)\n- Admin (/admin)\n\nSidebar style: 56px collapsed, expand on hover, cyan left-border on active item, JetBrains Mono. Match the MAGI nav pattern.\n\n**Add page-specific grid texture font link:**\n```html\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n```\n\n### 2. Voice Call (~/council-room/frontend/voice-call/index.html)\nRead the file, apply same Apex token swap:\n- Background: grid texture\n- Font: JetBrains Mono\n- Accent: cyan\n- Add inline sidebar nav (same as IT Support)\n\n### 3. Admin (~/council-room/frontend/admin.html)\nRead the file, apply same treatment:\n- Apex tokens\n- Grid texture\n- JetBrains Mono\n- Cyan accent\n- Add inline sidebar nav\n\n## Paul Simulator — D&D App (3 pages)\n\nThese need Apex polish while KEEPING the D&D fantasy flavor.\n\n### Design Direction:\n- **Background:** Dark (#0d121b) with grid texture — same as Apex\n- **Font:** JetBrains Mono for stats, combat, dice, game mechanics. But for flavor text (descriptions, lore), keep it readable.\n- **Accent color:** Golden/amber (#d4a73a or #fbbf24) for D&D flavor, NOT cyan. This keeps it feeling like a D&D app, not a developer tool.\n- **Cards/panels:** Same minimal Apex style (dark bg, subtle border)\n- **Dice animations:** Keep or enhance\n- **Character sheet:** Clean layout with stat blocks using monospace numbers\n\n### 4. Main D&D App (~/dnd-app/frontend/index.html — 1815 lines)\nRead the file. Apply:\n- Replace background with grid texture\n- Font: JetBrains Mono\n- Color scheme: dark Apex base + amber/gold accent for D&D\n- Cards: minimal Apex style\n- Stat numbers: monospace, large\n- Add sidebar nav (inline) with links to:\n  - MAGI Dashboard (/)\n  - D&D Main (current, active)\n  - D&D Guide (/dnd/guide)\n  - D&D Flow (/dnd/flow)\n\n### 5. D&D Guide (~/dnd-app/frontend/guide.html — 1009 lines)\nRead and apply same Apex + amber treatment.\nAdd inline sidebar nav.\n\n### 6. D&D Flow (~/dnd-app/frontend/flow.html — 322 lines)\nRead and apply same Apex + amber treatment.\nAdd inline sidebar nav.\n\n## Rules\n- Read EACH file completely