{"type":"message","id":"1a8f78ea","parentId":"18039c5f","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:45:02.729Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK — backend approve works fine when called correctly. The issue was the frontend — the approve button's API call might have had the wrong path or the response wasn't being checked properly. But now Kenny IS approved.\n\nThe issue was the double `JSON.stringify`. Look at the page code:\n```js\nawait api('admin/users/approve', { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify({ username, role }) });\n```\n\n`body` is passed as a string (already JSON.stringified). The `api()` function checks `typeof options.body === 'object'` — since it's a string, it won't auto-stringify, BUT it also won't set `Content-Type: application/json`. Without that header, the backend might not parse the body!"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_d7Uvwa174DBghAD967KUdC","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Fix: pass objects directly, let api() handle stringify\n# Also check if the error handling catches the response properly\ncat ~/magi-v2/frontend/users/index.html | grep -n \"JSON.stringify\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":285,"cacheRead":237860,"cacheWrite":464,"totalTokens":238610,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.007125,"cacheRead":0.11893,"cacheWrite":0.0029000000000000002,"total":0.12896000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775382293227}}
