{"type":"message","id":"b3bd2575","parentId":"249f016d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:08:25.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nUnderstood. ULTRAPLAN + 4 agent dispatch. Semua fitur MAGI harus REAL, bukan dummy. Let me fire up ULTRAPLAN dulu buat plan yang solid:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_aaHsPFzucRHwqH77ib3ULa","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"ultraplan-magi-real-features","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":1800,"task":"# ULTRAPLAN: Make ALL MAGI Features Actually Work — Zero Dummy Tolerance\n\nYou have up to 20 minutes. Do NOT execute anything. Produce a detailed, actionable plan for 4 parallel agents.\n\n## Problem\nMAGI v2 has 18 pages. Audit found that 6 are basically dummy/non-functional and 3 are partially real. Lucy wants EVERYTHING to actually work — no fake UI, no dummy data, no features that don't connect to the real backend.\n\n## Current State (from audit)\n\n### ✅ REAL (keep as-is, no changes needed):\n1. **Chat** — WebSocket, real Bedrock AI, works\n2. **Vault** — Obsidian file read/write, works\n3. **Files** — VPS file manager, works\n4. **Tasks** — Kanban CRUD, works\n5. **Leads** — 158K business data + map, works\n6. **Knowledge Base** — articles + search, works\n7. **Analytics** — token/cost tracking from MAGI chat, works\n8. **Users** — auth + role management, works\n9. **Login/Register** — works\n\n### ⚠️ PARTIALLY REAL (need to connect to OpenClaw):\n10. **Monitor** — Agent list is real but routing changes (WA handler) only save to MAGI DB, don't affect OpenClaw gateway. Need to: make routing changes actually call OpenClaw gateway API to change channel routing.\n11. **Settings > Models** — Can change model per agent but only affects MAGI chat, not OpenClaw. Need to: sync model changes to OpenClaw config.\n12. **Settings > Intensity** — Same issue. Only affects MAGI chat responses.\n\n### ❌ DUMMY (need to build for real):\n13. **Mission Control** — Shows cards but data is stale/static. Need to: fetch REAL system metrics (CPU, RAM, disk, PM2 processes, OpenClaw status, uptime) live.\n14. **Pipeline (CRM)** — Empty page. Need to: build a real sales pipeline that connects to Leads data. Stages: Lead → Contact → Meeting → Proposal → Won/Lost. CRUD for deals.\n15. **Broadcast** — UI exists but can't send real WA messages. Need to: connect to OpenClaw's WhatsApp message sending capability. Template system, recipient list, rate limiting, send log.\n16. **Reports** — Placeholder. Need to: auto-generate weekly reports from Analytics data, agent usage, cost breakdown, task completion. Store and display historical reports.\n17. **Notifications** — Always empty (0). Need to: create a real notification system that triggers on events (new user signup, task completion, agent error, high cost alert, cron failure).\n18. **ICat** — 0 contacts, empty templates. Need to: populate from WhatsApp contact history (if available), or make it a standalone CRM contacts system with import/export.\n\n## Architecture Context\n\n### OpenClaw Gateway\n- Running at localhost:18789 (proxied by Caddy)\n- Has its own config at ~/.openclaw/config.yaml\n- Gateway token available for API calls\n- Can send WhatsApp messages via the `message` tool\n- Has cron jobs, session management, agent config\n\n### MAGI v2 Backend\n- Fastify at localhost:3002\n- 2,400+ lines server.js\n- Data stored as JSON files in ~/magi-v2/backend/data/\n- Can make HTTP calls to OpenClaw gateway API\n\n### Key Integration Point\nMAGI backend needs to call OpenClaw's gateway API for:\n- Sending WhatsApp messages (Broadcast)\n- Changing channel routing (Monitor)\n- Getting real system status (Mission Control)\n- Syncing model config (Settings)\n\nThe OpenClaw gateway token can be read from the environment or config.\n\n## What to Read\nRead these files to understand current implementation:\n- ~/magi-v2/backend/server.js (full backend — find existing endpoints for each feature)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/mission/index.html (Mission Control page)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/pipeline/index.html (Pipeline CRM)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/broadcast/index.html (Broadcast)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/reports/index.html (Reports)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/notifications/index.html (Notifications)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/icat/index.html (ICat)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/monitor/index.html (Monitor — routing)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/settings/index.html (Settings — models)\n- ~/.openclaw/config.yaml (OpenClaw config structure)\n\n## Output Required\n\n### For each of the 9 broken/dummy features:\n1. What's wrong now (specific)\n2. What backend endpoints need to be added/modified\n3. What frontend changes needed\n4. How it connects to OpenClaw (if applicable)\n5. Data model (what gets stored where)\n6. Edge cases to handle\n\n### 4-Agent Execution Plan:\nSplit into 4 parallel streams with NO file conflicts:\n- **Agent 1:** Backend-only changes (new API endpoints, fix existing ones)\n- **Agent 2:** Mission Control + Monitor + Settings (system pages that need OpenClaw integration)\n- **Agent 3:** Pipeline CRM + ICat + Broadcast (business pages that need real functionality)\n- **Agent 4:** Reports + Notifications (automated systems that need event triggers)\n\n### For Mission Control specifically:\nMust show REAL data:\n- CPU/RAM/Disk usage (from `os` module or `top`/`free`/`df` commands)\n- PM2 process list with status, memory, uptime, restarts\n- OpenClaw gateway status (connected/disconnected, uptime)\n- Active WhatsApp/Telegram connections\n- Recent events (last 10 system events)\n- Auto-refresh every 30 seconds\n\n### For Pipeline CRM specifically:\nMust be a real sales funnel:\n- Stages: Lead → Contacted → Meeting → Proposal → Negotiation → Won → Lost\n- Deal cards: company name, contact, value, stage, last activity, notes\n- Drag between stages (or at least move via dropdown)\n- Link to Leads page (can import a lead as a deal)\n- Total value per stage\n- Win rate calculation\n\n### For Broadcast specifically:\nMust actually send WhatsApp messages:\n- Template creation with variables ({{name}}, {{company}})\n- Recipient list (manual entry or import from contacts)\n- Preview before send\n- Rate limiting (max 1 msg/second to avoid ban)\n- Send log with delivery status\n- Connect to OpenClaw's message sending (NOT direct WA API)\n\n### For Reports specifically:\nMust auto-generate from real data:\n- Weekly report: agent usage, total tokens, cost, top conversations, task progress\n- Pull from /api/analytics, /api/tasks, /api/sessions\n- PDF-style HTML report (viewable in browser)\n- Historical: store generated reports, list past reports\n- Optional: auto-generate on Sunday via cron\n\n### For Notifications specifically:\nMust trigger on real events:\n- New user registration (pending approval)\n- High token usage alert (>$X in a day)\n- Agent error in chat\n- Task overdue\n- System health warning (disk >90%, RAM >90%)\n- Store in notifications.json\n- Mark as read/unread\n- Badge count in sidebar\n\n## Rules\n- DO NOT execute anything\n- You MAY read files to understand current code\n- Be extremely specific about code changes\n- Every feature must work end-to-end (frontend → backend → real data)\n- No more dummy data, no more fake UI\n- Consider that this runs on a single 8GB VPS\n- OpenClaw gateway API is the bridge for WhatsApp operations"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":2028,"cacheRead":292874,"cacheWrite":389,"totalTokens":295294,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.0507,"cacheRead":0.14643699999999998,"cacheWrite":0.0024312500000000003,"total":0.19958325}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775401653852}}
