s\n- **Fixed routing labels:** \"WhatsApp Handler\" → \"MAGI Send-As Agent\", \"Telegram Handler\" → \"MAGI Send-As Agent (Telegram)\"\n- **Added info text** under each routing card: \"Controls which agent voice MAGI uses when sending messages. OpenClaw gateway routing is separate.\"\n- **Added Gateway Status indicator** at top of page, fetching from `GET /api/system/status` — shows \"🟢 OpenClaw Gateway: Connected\" or \"🔴 Disconnected\" with animated dot\n\n### 3. Settings (`settings/index.html`) — Small additions\n- Added clarification under **Global Model Mode**: \"Model changes affect MAGI chat responses only. OpenClaw gateway uses its own model config.\"\n- Added clarification under **Agent Configuration**: Same model config note\n- Added clarification under **Intensity Control**: \"Intensity affects MAGI chat verbosity only.\"\n- All notes styled as subtle info boxes with amber background\n<<<END_UNTRUSTED_CHILD_RESULT>>>\n\nStats: runtime 5m57s • tokens 19.1k (in 18 / out 19.1k) • prompt/cache 73.1k\n\nAction:\nA completed subagent task is ready for user delivery. Convert the result above into your normal assistant voice and send that user-facing update now. Keep this internal context private (don't mention system/log/stats/session details or announce type)."}],"timestamp":1775402467100,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:e55af23e-653b-4ba3-9bb4-a07f71a33373","sourceChannel":"webchat","sourceTool":"subagent_announce"}}}
