{"type":"message","id":"e5a6f950","parentId":"dad27177","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:58:21.327Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_L3ZxnGgKgj4KP4zp3e5cje","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ULTRAPLAN: D&D Paul Simulator — TOTAL UI/UX REMODEL + AI Assistant\n\n**Author:** Michael (ULTRAPLAN subagent)  \n**Date:** 2026-04-05  \n**Status:** PLAN — Do NOT execute until Lucy approves  \n**Philosophy:** K.I.S.S. — \"aku ingin orang bodoh pun paham pake aplikasi ini\"\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. [Executive Summary](#1-executive-summary)\n2. [New App Architecture](#2-new-app-architecture)\n3. [AI Assistant Specification](#3-ai-assistant-specification)\n4. [UI Component Inventory](#4-ui-component-inventory)\n5. [Onboarding Flow](#5-onboarding-flow)\n6. [CSS / Design System](#6-css--design-system)\n7. [4-Agent Execution Plan](#7-4-agent-execution-plan)\n8. [Migration Plan](#8-migration-plan)\n9. [Mobile-First Responsive](#9-mobile-first-responsive)\n10. [Risk Assessment](#10-risk-assessment)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\n### What We're Doing\nTransforming a 3-page, 9-sidebar-nav D&D companion app into a single-page, 4-tab, mobile-first app with an integrated AI assistant. Merging `guide.html` and `flow.html` into `index.html`. Replacing the sidebar nav with a bottom tab bar.\n\n### Key Decisions\n| Decision | Choice | Why |\n|----------|--------|-----|\n| Navigation | Bottom tab bar (4 tabs) | Mobile thumb-friendly, K.I.S.S. |\n| AI Integration | New chat panel + backend endpoint | Uses existing Bedrock via Council |\n| Pages | Single `index.html` | Zero page switches |\n| Sub-features | Slide-in panels (not pages, not modals) | Full-screen feel, back button |\n| Design | Apex Dark + Amber (refined) | Already partially done, D&D fantasy feel |\n| CSS | Complete rewrite of `styles.css` | Current 6130 lines is unmaintainable |\n\n### What Gets Killed\n- `guide.html` → content becomes contextual help tooltips + \"Guide\" panel in More tab\n- `flow.html` → content is purely documentation, not user-facing; archive it\n- Left sidebar nav (desktop) → replaced by bottom tab bar on all screens\n- MAGI sidebar (Apex sidebar from parent app) → removed from D&D pages\n- 9 sidebar nav items → 4 bottom tabs\n- Spectator mode → moves to More tab (low priority feature)\n\n### What Gets Added\n- **AI Assistant tab** (chat with session context)\n- **Bottom tab bar** (Play, Party, AI, More)\n- **Slide-in panel system** (for sub-features)\n- **Solo Adventure** flow (AI DM, already partially built)\n- **Contextual help** (? icons with tooltips)\n\n---\n\n## 2. New App Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Single `index.html` Structure\n\n```\nindex.html\n├── <head> (fonts, styles.css)\n├── <body>\n│   ├── #login-screen (onboarding — visible when not authenticated)\n│   │   ├── .onboard-hero (dragon + title)\n│   │   ├── .onboard-buttons (3 big buttons: Create Game, Join Game, Solo)\n│   │   ├── #create-flow (step-by-step DM creation)\n│   │   ├── #join-flow (PIN entry for players)\n│   │   └── #solo-flow (character select → genre → go)\n│   │\n│   ├── #app-screen (main app — visible after auth)\n│   │   ├── #app-header (room info bar — PIN, name, role)\n│   │   ├── #tab-content (main content area)\n│   │   │   ├── #tab-play (dice + initiative + quick actions)\n│   │   │   ├── #tab-party (party overview + character sheets)\n│   │   │   ├── #tab-ai (AI assistant chat)\n│   │   │   └── #tab-more (grid of feature cards)\n│   │   ├── #panel-container (slide-in panels from More)\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"spells\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"monsters\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"npcs\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"map\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"notes\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"guide\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"history\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"settings\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"wiki\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"encounters\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"arena\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"journal\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"relationships\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"compendium\"]\n│   │   │   ├── .panel[data-panel=\"rulebook\"]\n│   │   │   └── .panel[data-panel=\"chat\"] (in-game text chat)\n│   │   └── #bottom-tabs (fixed tab bar)\n│   │\n│   └── <script src=\"/dnd/app.js\"></script>\n```\n\n\n[1386 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775404701293}}
{"type":"message","id":"a5bf7b16","parentId":"e5a6f950","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:58:59.611Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — plan is detailed. Now dispatch:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_8b5GbpPYp8rUsCIQysqxRj","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"dnd-agent1-backend","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# D&D Remodel — Agent 1: Backend (AI Chat Endpoint)\n\nAdd AI Assistant endpoint to ~/dnd-app/backend/server.js. Do NOT touch frontend files.\n\n## Read First\n- ~/dnd-app/backend/server.js (full file — understand existing patterns, especially POST /api/rooms/:pin/summary which already uses Bedrock)\n- ~/dnd-app/backend/bestiary-data.js\n- ~/dnd-app/backend/spells-data.js\n\n## Deliverable: POST /api/rooms/:pin/ai-chat\n\n### Context Gathering\nBefore calling Bedrock, gather session context:\n```javascript\nfunction gatherSessionContext(room) {\n  const ctx = []\n  \n  // Party info\n  if (room.players?.length) {\n    ctx.push('## Current Party')\n    for (const p of room.players) {\n      const char = p.character || {}\n      ctx.push(`- **${p.name}** (${char.race || '?'} ${char.class || '?'} Lv${char.level || 1}) HP: ${char.hp || '?'}/${char.maxHp || '?'} AC: ${char.ac || '?'}`)\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // Initiative order (if combat active)\n  if (room.initiative?.length) {\n    ctx.push('\\n## Initiative Order')\n    room.initiative.forEach((entry, i) => {\n      ctx.push(`${i + 1}. ${entry.name} (${entry.initiative})${entry.current ? ' ← CURRENT TURN' : ''}`)\n    })\n  }\n  \n  // Recent dice rolls (last 10)\n  if (room.rolls?.length) {\n    ctx.push('\\n## Recent Dice Rolls')\n    room.rolls.slice(-10).forEach(r => {\n      ctx.push(`- ${r.player}: ${r.notation} = **${r.total}** ${r.details || ''}`)\n    })\n  }\n  \n  // Session notes\n  if (room.notes) {\n    ctx.push('\\n## Session Notes')\n    ctx.push(room.notes)\n  }\n  \n  return ctx.join('\\n')\n}\n```\n\n### System Prompt\n```\nYou are a D&D 5e (2024 rules) game assistant. You help both DMs and Players.\n\nYour knowledge:\n- All D&D 2024 Player's Handbook rules\n- Monsters, spells, items, conditions\n- Creative encounter design\n- NPC roleplay and voices\n- Rules interpretation\n\nCurrent session context:\n{sessionContext}\n\nGuidelines:\n- Be concise but helpful\n- Use D&D terminology correctly\n- When suggesting encounters, consider party level and composition\n- When asked about rules, cite the relevant rule\n- For roleplay, be creative and engaging\n- If asked to make a decision for a player, suggest options instead\n- Respond in the same language the user writes in\n- Use emoji for flavor (⚔️ for combat, 🎲 for dice, 🧙 for magic, etc.)\n```\n\n### Endpoint Implementation\n```javascript\n// AI Chat for D&D sessions\nconst AI_CHAT_HISTORY = {} // roomPin → [{role, content}]\n\napp.post('/api/rooms/:pin/ai-chat', async (req, res) => {\n  const { message } = req.body\n  if (!message) return res.status(400).json({ ok: false, error: 'Message required' })\n  \n  const room = findRoomByAnyPin(req.params.pin)\n  if (!room) return res.status(404).json({ ok: false, error: 'Room not found' })\n  \n  const roomPin = room.dmPin || req.params.pin\n  \n  // Initialize history\n  if (!AI_CHAT_HISTORY[roomPin]) AI_CHAT_HISTORY[roomPin] = []\n  const history = AI_CHAT_HISTORY[roomPin]\n  \n  // Gather context\n  const context = gatherSessionContext(room)\n  \n  // Add user message\n  history.push({ role: 'user', content: message })\n  \n  // Keep last 20 messages\n  if (history.length > 20) history.splice(0, history.length - 20)\n  \n  // Build messages for Bedrock\n  const systemPrompt = `You are a D&D 5e (2024 rules) game assistant...` // full prompt above\n  \n  // Call Bedrock (same pattern as /api/rooms/:pin/summary)\n  try {\n    const response = await callBedrock(systemPrompt + '\\n\\n' + context, history)\n    history.push({ role: 'assistant', content: response })\n    res.json({ ok: true, response, historyLength: history.length })\n  } catch (e) {\n    res.status(500).json({ ok: false, error: e.message })\n  }\n})\n\n// Clear AI chat history\napp.delete('/api/rooms/:pin/ai-chat', (req, res) => {\n  const room = findRoomByAnyPin(req.params.pin)\n  if (!room) return res.status(404).json({ ok: false, error: 'Room not found' })\n  const roomPin = room.dmPin || req.params.pin\n  AI_CHAT_HISTORY[roomPin] = []\n  res.json({ ok: true })\n})\n```\n\n### Important: Reuse Existing Bedrock Code\nThe existing `POST /api/rooms/:pin/summary` already calls Bedrock. Find that function and reuse the same Bedrock client/invocation pattern. Do NOT create a new Bedrock client — reuse the existing one.\n\nLook for the BedrockRuntimeClient setup and the InvokeModelWithResponseStream pattern.\n\n### Rate Limiting\nAdd simple rate limit: max 1 AI request per 3 seconds per room.\n```javascript\nconst AI_RATE_LIMIT = {}\n// Before calling Bedrock:\nconst now = Date.now()\nif (AI_RATE_LIMIT[roomPin] && now - AI_RATE_LIMIT[roomPin] < 3000) {\n  return res.status(429).json({ ok: false, error: 'Please wait a moment before asking again' })\n}\nAI_RATE_LIMIT[roomPin] = now\n```\n\n### Also: findRoomByAnyPin helper\nCheck if this already exists. If not, create one that searches rooms by dmPin OR player pin:\n```javascript\nfunction findRoomByAnyPin(pin) {\n  // Check DM pins\n  if (rooms[pin]) return rooms[pin]\n  // Check player pins\n  for (const room of Object.values(rooms)) {\n    if (room.players?.some(p => p.pin === pin)) return room\n  }\n  return null\n}\n```\n\n## Rules\n- Read server.js FULLY first\n- Reuse existing Bedrock client (do not create new AWS client)\n- Follow existing code patterns (error handling, response format)\n- Do NOT modify frontend files\n- Test that PM2 restart works after changes\n- Keep all existing endpoints working"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":1857,"cacheRead":335276,"cacheWrite":1548,"totalTokens":338682,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.046425,"cacheRead":0.16763799999999998,"cacheWrite":0.009675000000000001,"total":0.22374299999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775404701338}}
{"type":"message","id":"935dac01","parentId":"a5bf7b16","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:59:00.893Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_8b5GbpPYp8rUsCIQysqxRj","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:4653de46-fa90-4ee2-9241-a252d53d1c0b\",\n  \"runId\": \"9ef244d9-4380-49cb-a7b0-1d4f4ede5398\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:4653de46-fa90-4ee2-9241-a252d53d1c0b","runId":"9ef244d9-4380-49cb-a7b0-1d4f4ede5398","mode":"run","note":"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775404740870}}
{"type":"message","id":"8296645e","parentId":"935dac01","timestamp":"2026-04-05T16:00:00.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_85FWLsBjaAtfaOCHarJSzj","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"dnd-agent2-layout","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# D&D Remodel — Agent 2: Frontend Layout + CSS Rewrite\n\nComplete rewrite of ~/dnd-app/frontend/index.html structure and ~/dnd-app/frontend/styles.css.\n\n## Read First\n- ~/dnd-app/frontend/index.html (current 1852 lines)\n- ~/dnd-app/frontend/styles.css (current 6130 lines)\n- ~/dnd-app/ULTRAPLAN-REMODEL.md (the full plan)\n\n## CRITICAL: Understand the Current JS\nThe current index.html has a `<script src=\"/dnd/app.js\">` or inline JS that references specific DOM element IDs. You need to PRESERVE all critical IDs that the JS references, or the app will break. Read the JS carefully and keep all IDs that are used.\n\nActually — check if there's a separate app.js:\n```bash\nls ~/dnd-app/frontend/*.js\n```\nIf not, the JS is inline in index.html. In that case, keep ALL the JS code but restructure the HTML around it.\n\n## New HTML Structure\n\nReplace the current sidebar-based layout with a bottom-tab layout:\n\n```html\n<body>\n  <!-- LOGIN SCREEN (visible before auth) -->\n  <div id=\"login-screen\">\n    <div class=\"onboard\">\n      <div class=\"onboard-hero\">\n        <div class=\"onboard-icon\">🐉</div>\n        <h1>Paul Simulator</h1>\n        <p>D&D 2024 Companion</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"onboard-buttons\">\n        <button class=\"big-btn gold\" id=\"show-create-btn\">⚔️ Create Game</button>\n        <button class=\"big-btn outline\" id=\"enter-game-btn\">🎲 Join Game</button>\n        <button class=\"big-btn ghost\" id=\"solo-adventure-btn\">🧙 Solo Adventure</button>\n      </div>\n      <!-- Keep existing create/join/solo panels but restyle -->\n      <div id=\"create-panel\" class=\"onboard-panel\">...</div>\n      <div id=\"pin-login-panel\" class=\"onboard-panel\">...</div>\n      <div id=\"spectate-panel\" class=\"onboard-panel\" style=\"display:none\">...</div>\n      <div id=\"room-created-panel\" class=\"onboard-panel\">...</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- APP SCREEN (visible after auth) -->\n  <div id=\"app-screen\" style=\"display:none\">\n    <!-- Header bar -->\n    <div class=\"app-header\">\n      <span class=\"header-pin\" id=\"display-pin\"></span>\n      <span class=\"header-name\" id=\"display-name\"></span>\n      <span class=\"header-role\" id=\"display-role\"></span>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Tab content area -->\n    <div class=\"tab-content\">\n      <div class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"tab-play\">\n        <!-- Agent 3 builds this -->\n        <div class=\"placeholder\">Play tab — dice, initiative, quick actions</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"tab-party\">\n        <!-- Agent 3 builds this -->\n        <div class=\"placeholder\">Party tab — characters, HP</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"tab-ai\">\n        <!-- Agent 4 builds this -->\n        <div class=\"placeholder\">AI Assistant</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"tab-more\">\n        <!-- Agent 4 builds this -->\n        <div class=\"placeholder\">More features</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Panel overlay (for sub-features from More tab) -->\n    <div id=\"panel-overlay\" class=\"panel-overlay\" style=\"display:none\">\n      <div class=\"panel-header\">\n        <button class=\"panel-back\" onclick=\"closePanel()\">← Back</button>\n        <span class=\"panel-title\" id=\"panel-title\"></span>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"panel-body\" id=\"panel-body\"></div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Bottom tab bar (FIXED) -->\n    <nav class=\"bottom-tabs\">\n      <button class=\"tab-btn active\" data-tab=\"play\" onclick=\"switchTab('play')\">\n        <span class=\"tab-icon\">🎲</span>\n        <span class=\"tab-label\">Play</span>\n      </button>\n      <button class=\"tab-btn\" data-tab=\"party\" onclick=\"switchTab('party')\">\n        <span class=\"tab-icon\">📋</span>\n        <span class=\"tab-label\">Party</span>\n      </button>\n      <button class=\"tab-btn\" data-tab=\"ai\" onclick=\"switchTab('ai')\">\n        <span class=\"tab-icon\">🤖</span>\n        <span class=\"tab-label\">AI</span>\n      </button>\n      <button class=\"tab-btn\" data-tab=\"more\" onclick=\"switchTab('more')\">\n        <span class=\"tab-icon\">☰</span>\n        <span class=\"tab-label\">More</span>\n      </button>\n    </nav>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Keep ALL existing JS (inline or app.js) -->\n</body>\n```\n\n## New styles.css — Complete Rewrite\n\nReplace the 6130-line CSS with a clean Apex Dark + Amber system:\n\n### Color Tokens\n```css\n:root {\n  --bg: #0d121b;\n  --bg-surface: #0f141f;\n  --bg-card: #131a27;\n  --bg-hover: rgba(212, 167, 58, 0.05);\n  --bg-active: rgba(212, 167, 58, 0.08);\n  --border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);\n  --border-strong: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.11);\n  --text: #c9d1d9;\n  --text-bright: #f3f4f6;\n  --text-muted: #6e7681;\n  --text-dim: #424854;\n  --gold: #d4a73a;\n  --gold-dim: rgba(212, 167, 58, 0.4);\n  --gold-bg: rgba(212, 167, 58, 0.08);\n  --success: #86efac;\n  --danger: #fca5a5;\n  --warning: #fde047;\n  --font-display: 'Cinzel', serif;\n  --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n  --radius: 10px;\n  --ease: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);\n}\n```\n\n### Key CSS Components\n```css\n/* Grid texture background */\nbody::before { content:''; position:fixed; inset:0; pointer-events:none; z-index:0;\n  background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.024) 1px, transparent 1px),\n  linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.024) 1px, transparent 1px);\n  background-size: 48px 48px; }\n\n/* Bottom tab bar */\n.bottom-tabs { position: fixed; bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 64px;\n  background: var(--bg-surface); border-top: 1px solid var(--border);\n  display: flex; z-index: 50; padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom, 0); }\n.tab-btn { flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center; gap: 2px; background: none; border: none;\n  color: var(--text-dim); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; cursor: pointer; }\n.tab-btn.active { color: var(--gold); }\n.tab-icon { font-size: 22px; }\n\n/* Tab content */\n.tab-content { position: fixed; top: 44px; bottom: 64px; left: 0; right: 0; overflow: hidden; }\n.tab-pane { display: none; height: 100%; overflow-y: auto; padding: 16px; }\n.tab-pane.active { display: block; }\n\n/* Panel overlay */\n.panel-overlay { position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 100; background: var(--bg);\n  transform: translateX(100%); transition: transform 0.3s var(--ease); }\n.panel-overlay.open { transform: translateX(0); }\n.panel-header { height: 44px; display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 0 12px;\n  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }\n.panel-back { background: none; border: none; color: var(--gold); font-family: var(--font-mono);\n  font-size: 13px; cursor: pointer; }\n.panel-body { height: calc(100% - 44px); overflow-y: auto; padding: 16px; }\n\n/* App header */\n.app-header { height: 44px; background: var(--bg-surface); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n  display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 0 16px; gap: 12px; font-size: 12px; }\n\n/* Onboarding */\n.onboard { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center;\n  min-height: 100vh; padding: 24px; }\n.onboard-hero { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px; }\n.onboard-icon { font-size: 80px; margin-bottom: 16px; }\n.onboard-hero h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 32px; color: var(--gold); }\n.onboard-hero p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 8px; }\n.onboard-buttons { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; width: 100%; max-width: 320px; }\n.big-btn { padding: 16px; border-radius: var(--radius); font-family: var(--font-mono);\n  font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid; text-align: center; }\n.big-btn.gold { background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(212,167,58,0.15), rgba(212,167,58,0.08));\n  border-color: var(--gold-dim); color: var(--gold); }\n.big-btn.outline { background: transparent; border-color: var(--border-strong); color: var(--text); }\n.big-btn.ghost { background: transparent; border-color: transparent; color: var(--text-muted); }\n\n/* Cards */\n.card { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 16px; }\n\n/* Scrollbar */\n::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; }\n::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: rgba(212,167,58,0.15); border-radius: 4px; }\n```\n\n### Tab Switching JS (add to the script section)\n```javascript\nfunction switchTab(tabId) {\n  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-pane').forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));\n  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));\n  document.getElementById('tab-' + tabId)?.classList.add('active');\n  document.querySelector(`.tab-btn[data-tab=\"${tabId}\"]`)?.classList.add('active');\n}\n\nfunction openPanel(title, contentHtml) {\n  document.getElementById('panel-title').textContent = title;\n  document.getElementById('panel-body').innerHTML = contentHtml;\n  const overlay = document.getElementById('panel-overlay');\n  overlay.style.display = 'block';\n  requestAnimationFrame(() => overlay.classList.add('open'));\n}\n\nfunction closePanel() {\n  const overlay = document.getElementById('panel-overlay');\n  overlay.classList.remove('open');\n  setTimeout(() => { overlay.style.display = 'none'; }, 300);\n}\n```\n\n## CRITICAL Rules\n- KEEP all existing DOM element IDs that JS references (login-pin, enter-game-btn, show-create-btn, etc.)\n- KEEP all existing JS code — just restructure the HTML around it\n- Remove the old sidebar (#sidebar and all nav-*-btn elements) — remap to bottom tabs\n- Remove MAGI sidebar (the Apex nav from parent app — remove <div id=\"nav\"></div> and renderNav calls)\n- Add Google Fonts link for Cinzel: `<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">`\n- The tab-play, tab-party, tab-ai, tab-more divs are PLACEHOLDERS — Agent 3 and 4 will fill them\n- Your job is the STRUCTURE, LAYOUT, CSS, and TAB SYSTEM only\n- Test HTML structure is balanced"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":3483,"cacheRead":336824,"cacheWrite":2058,"totalTokens":342366,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.087075,"cacheRead":0.168412,"cacheWrite":0.0128625,"total":0.2683545}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775404740911}}
{"type":"message","id":"9786fcf3","parentId":"8296645e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T16:00:02.309Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_85FWLsBjaAtfaOCHarJSzj","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:819490b6-7c16-4b95-8ca2-5d225ad5928b\",\n  \"runId\": \"568f0760-11b0-483c-9121-5a99a165a21c\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:819490b6-7c16-4b95-8ca2-5d225ad5928b","runId":"568f0760-11b0-483c-9121-5a99a165a21c","mode":"run","note":"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775404802203}}
{"type":"message","id":"966963b6","parentId":"9786fcf3","timestamp":"2026-04-05T16:00:53.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_S6iVKxOS2GzVWqid8zaxR5","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"dnd-agent3-play-party","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# D&D Remodel — Agent 3: Play Tab + Party Tab Content\n\nBuild the content for the Play and Party tabs in ~/dnd-app/frontend/index.html.\n\n## Read First\n- ~/dnd-app/frontend/index.html (find #tab-play and #tab-party placeholders)\n- ~/dnd-app/ULTRAPLAN-REMODEL.md (sections 4.1 Play Tab and 4.2 Party Tab)\n- Look at existing dice roller, initiative tracker, and character sheet code in the current file\n\n## IMPORTANT: Reuse Existing JS\nThe current index.html already has dice rolling, initiative tracking, and character sheet JS. You need to:\n1. Find the existing functions (rollDice, addToInitiative, renderCharacter, etc.)\n2. Keep those functions\n3. Just rebuild the HTML that they render into\n\n## Play Tab (#tab-play)\n\n### Dice Roller Section\n```html\n<div class=\"play-section\">\n  <h3 class=\"section-title\">🎲 Dice Roller</h3>\n  <div class=\"dice-grid\">\n    <button class=\"dice-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d4')\">d4</button>\n    <button class=\"dice-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d6')\">d6</button>\n    <button class=\"dice-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d8')\">d8</button>\n    <button class=\"dice-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d10')\">d10</button>\n    <button class=\"dice-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d12')\">d12</button>\n    <button class=\"dice-btn d20\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d20')\">d20</button>\n  </div>\n  \n  <!-- Custom roll -->\n  <div class=\"custom-roll\">\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"custom-dice\" placeholder=\"e.g., 2d6+3\" class=\"dice-input\">\n    <button class=\"roll-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice(document.getElementById('custom-dice').value)\">Roll</button>\n  </div>\n  \n  <!-- Result display -->\n  <div class=\"dice-result\" id=\"dice-result\" style=\"display:none\">\n    <div class=\"result-number\" id=\"result-number\"></div>\n    <div class=\"result-detail\" id=\"result-detail\"></div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <!-- Roll history -->\n  <div class=\"roll-history\" id=\"roll-history\"></div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### CSS for Dice\n```css\n.dice-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px; }\n.dice-btn { padding: 20px; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);\n  background: var(--bg-card); color: var(--text); font-family: var(--font-mono);\n  font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s;\n  min-height: 64px; text-align: center; }\n.dice-btn:hover { border-color: var(--gold-dim); background: var(--gold-bg); color: var(--gold); }\n.dice-btn:active { transform: scale(0.95); }\n.dice-btn.d20 { grid-column: span 3; background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(212,167,58,0.1), rgba(212,167,58,0.04));\n  border-color: var(--gold-dim); color: var(--gold); font-size: 24px; }\n\n.dice-result { text-align: center; padding: 24px; margin: 12px 0;\n  background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); }\n.result-number { font-size: 64px; font-weight: 700; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--gold);\n  animation: diceReveal 0.3s var(--ease); }\n.result-number.crit { color: var(--success); text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(134,239,172,0.5); }\n.result-number.fumble { color: var(--danger); }\n.result-detail { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 8px; }\n\n@keyframes diceReveal { from { transform: scale(0.5) rotate(180deg); opacity: 0; } to { transform: scale(1) rotate(0); opacity: 1; } }\n\n.custom-roll { display: flex; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px; }\n.dice-input { flex: 1; padding: 10px 12px; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border: 1px solid var(--border);\n  border-radius: var(--radius); color: var(--text); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 14px; }\n.roll-btn { padding: 10px 20px; background: var(--gold-bg); border: 1px solid var(--gold-dim);\n  color: var(--gold); border-radius: var(--radius); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }\n\n.roll-history { max-height: 200px; overflow-y: auto; }\n.roll-item { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 6px 0;\n  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 12px; }\n```\n\n### Quick Actions Section\n```html\n<div class=\"play-section\">\n  <h3 class=\"section-title\">⚔️ Quick Actions</h3>\n  <div class=\"quick-actions\">\n    <button class=\"action-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d20')\">🎯 Attack Roll</button>\n    <button class=\"action-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d20')\">🛡️ Saving Throw</button>\n    <button class=\"action-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('1d20')\">🔍 Skill Check</button>\n    <button class=\"action-btn\" onclick=\"rollDice('2d6')\">💥 Damage (2d6)</button>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### Initiative Tracker Section\n```html\n<div class=\"play-section\" id=\"initiative-section\">\n  <h3 class=\"section-title\">⚡ Initiative</h3>\n  <div id=\"initiative-list\"></div>\n  <div class=\"init-actions\">\n    <button class=\"action-btn\" onclick=\"rollInitiativeAll()\">🎲 Roll All</button>\n    <button class=\"action-btn\" onclick=\"nextTurn()\">▶ Next Turn</button>\n    <button class=\"action-btn danger\" onclick=\"clearInitiative()\">🗑️ Clear</button>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n## Party Tab (#tab-party)\n\n### Party Overview\n```html\n<div class=\"party-header\">\n  <h3 class=\"section-title\">📋 Party</h3>\n  <button class=\"add-btn\" onclick=\"showAddCharacter()\">+ Add Character</button>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"party-list\" class=\"party-list\">\n  <!-- Rendered by JS — each character card: -->\n  <!--\n  <div class=\"char-card\" onclick=\"openCharacterSheet(id)\">\n    <div class=\"char-top\">\n      <span class=\"char-name\">Aragorn</span>\n      <span class=\"char-class\">Human Fighter Lv5</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"char-hp-bar\">\n      <div class=\"hp-fill\" style=\"width:75%\"></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"char-stats\">\n      <span>HP: 38/50</span>\n      <span>AC: 18</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  -->\n</div>\n```\n\n### CSS for Party\n```css\n.party-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }\n.char-card { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius);\n  padding: 14px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s; }\n.char-card:hover { border-color: var(--gold-dim); }\n.char-top { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 8px; }\n.char-name { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-bright); }\n.char-class { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-muted); }\n.char-hp-bar { height: 6px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius: 3px; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 6px; }\n.hp-fill { height: 100%; border-radius: 3px; transition: width 0.3s, background 0.3s; }\n.hp-fill.high { background: var(--success); }\n.hp-fill.mid { background: var(--warning); }\n.hp-fill.low { background: var(--danger); }\n.char-stats { display: flex; gap: 16px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-muted); font-family: var(--font-mono); }\n```\n\n## Rules\n- Read the EXISTING index.html JS code to find current function names for dice/initiative/character\n- Reuse those functions — just provide new HTML structure they render into\n- If functions reference old DOM IDs, update the HTML to use those same IDs\n- Add CSS to styles.css (append, don't overwrite — Agent 2 handles the base)\n- Wait — actually Agent 2 is rewriting styles.css. So put your CSS in a <style> tag inside the tab-play and tab-party sections, or append to styles.css AFTER Agent 2's base styles.\n- Actually simplest: put all your CSS inline in <style> blocks within index.html, inside the tab-pane divs. This avoids file conflicts with Agent 2.\n- Make all buttons minimum 48px touch target\n- Font: JetBrains Mono for stats, Cinzel for character names\n- Dice result: BIG number (64px), gold color, animation on roll\n- HP bars: green >50%, yellow 25-50%, red <25%"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":2780,"cacheRead":338882,"cacheWrite":3681,"totalTokens":345344,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0695,"cacheRead":0.16944099999999998,"cacheWrite":0.023006250000000002,"total":0.26195225}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775404802339}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c75765a","parentId":"966963b6","timestamp":"2026-04-05T16:00:54.433Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_S6iVKxOS2GzVWqid8zaxR5","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:952b259b-e1db-4acf-b653-4601dcf5102f\",\n  \"runId\": \"5f27e958-4105-47cd-ab9b-fb4dd1b37ed9\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:952b259b-e1db-4acf-b653-4601dcf5102f","runId":"5f27e958-4105-47cd-ab9b-fb4dd1b37ed9","mode":"run","note":"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775404854399}}
{"type":"message","id":"20c3141d","parentId":"0c75765a","timestamp":"2026-04-05T16:02:01.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_5IrEluRPtZ7xTepRduHyTY","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"dnd-agent4-ai-more","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# D&D Remodel — Agent 4: AI Tab + More Tab Content\n\nBuild the AI Assistant chat and the More tab feature grid in ~/dnd-app/frontend/index.html.\n\n## Read First\n- ~/dnd-app/frontend/index.html (find #tab-ai and #tab-more placeholders)\n- ~/dnd-app/frontend/guide.html (content to merge into Guide panel)\n- ~/dnd-app/ULTRAPLAN-REMODEL.md (sections 3 AI Assistant and 4.3-4.4)\n- ~/dnd-app/backend/server.js (find existing spell/monster lookup, understand PIN auth)\n\n## AI Tab (#tab-ai)\n\n### Chat Interface\n```html\n<div class=\"ai-container\">\n  <div class=\"ai-header\">\n    <span class=\"ai-title\">🤖 AI Assistant</span>\n    <button class=\"ai-clear\" onclick=\"clearAiChat()\">Clear</button>\n  </div>\n  \n  <!-- Suggested prompts (show when chat is empty) -->\n  <div class=\"ai-suggestions\" id=\"ai-suggestions\">\n    <p class=\"ai-hint\">Ask me anything about D&D!</p>\n    <div class=\"suggest-grid\">\n      <button class=\"suggest-btn\" onclick=\"askAi('Suggest a random encounter for my party')\">🎲 Random Encounter</button>\n      <button class=\"suggest-btn\" onclick=\"askAi('Help me create an interesting NPC')\">👤 NPC Idea</button>\n      <button class=\"suggest-btn\" onclick=\"askAi('What are my best options in combat right now?')\">⚔️ Combat Advice</button>\n      <button class=\"suggest-btn\" onclick=\"askAi('Explain a rule I am confused about')\">📖 Rule Check</button>\n      <button class=\"suggest-btn\" onclick=\"askAi('Describe the scene around us')\">🏰 Scene Description</button>\n      <button class=\"suggest-btn\" onclick=\"askAi('Give me a puzzle or riddle for my players')\">🧩 Puzzle Idea</button>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <!-- Chat messages -->\n  <div class=\"ai-messages\" id=\"ai-messages\"></div>\n  \n  <!-- Input -->\n  <div class=\"ai-input-row\">\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"ai-input\" class=\"ai-input\" placeholder=\"Ask the AI...\" \n      onkeydown=\"if(event.key==='Enter' && !event.shiftKey){event.preventDefault();askAi()}\">\n    <button class=\"ai-send\" id=\"ai-send\" onclick=\"askAi()\">➤</button>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### AI Chat JS\n```javascript\nasync function askAi(presetMsg) {\n  const input = document.getElementById('ai-input');\n  const msg = presetMsg || input.value.trim();\n  if (!msg) return;\n  \n  if (!presetMsg) input.value = '';\n  \n  // Hide suggestions\n  document.getElementById('ai-suggestions').style.display = 'none';\n  \n  // Add user message\n  addAiMessage('user', msg);\n  \n  // Show typing indicator\n  const typingId = addAiMessage('typing', '');\n  \n  // Disable send\n  document.getElementById('ai-send').disabled = true;\n  \n  try {\n    // Use the current room PIN\n    const pin = currentPin || sessionStorage.getItem('dnd_pin');\n    const resp = await fetch(`/dnd-api/rooms/${pin}/ai-chat`, {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ message: msg })\n    });\n    const data = await resp.json();\n    \n    // Remove typing indicator\n    removeAiMessage(typingId);\n    \n    if (data.ok) {\n      addAiMessage('assistant', data.response);\n    } else {\n      addAiMessage('error', data.error || 'Failed to get response');\n    }\n  } catch (e) {\n    removeAiMessage(typingId);\n    addAiMessage('error', 'Connection error: ' + e.message);\n  }\n  \n  document.getElementById('ai-send').disabled = false;\n  input.focus();\n}\n\nfunction addAiMessage(role, text) {\n  const container = document.getElementById('ai-messages');\n  const id = 'ai-msg-' + Date.now() + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2,6);\n  const div = document.createElement('div');\n  div.id = id;\n  div.className = 'ai-msg ai-' + role;\n  \n  if (role === 'typing') {\n    div.innerHTML = '<div class=\"typing-dots\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>';\n  } else if (role === 'error') {\n    div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"ai-error\">⚠️ ' + escapeHtml(text) + '</span>';\n  } else {\n    // Simple markdown: bold, italic, code, lists\n    let html = escapeHtml(text)\n      .replace(/\\*\\*(.+?)\\*\\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>')\n      .replace(/\\*(.+?)\\*/g, '<em>$1</em>')\n      .replace(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code>$1</code>')\n      .replace(/\\n/g, '<br>');\n    div.innerHTML = html;\n  }\n  \n  container.appendChild(div);\n  container.scrollTop = container.scrollHeight;\n  return id;\n}\n\nfunction removeAiMessage(id) {\n  document.getElementById(id)?.remove();\n}\n\nfunction clearAiChat() {\n  document.getElementById('ai-messages').innerHTML = '';\n  document.getElementById('ai-suggestions').style.display = 'block';\n  // Also clear server-side history\n  const pin = currentPin || sessionStorage.getItem('dnd_pin');\n  if (pin) fetch(`/dnd-api/rooms/${pin}/ai-chat`, { method: 'DELETE' }).catch(() => {});\n}\n\nfunction escapeHtml(s) { return s.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;'); }\n```\n\n### AI Chat CSS\n```css\n.ai-container { display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: 100%; }\n.ai-header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding-bottom: 12px;\n  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 12px; }\n.ai-title { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; }\n.ai-clear { background: none; border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-muted);\n  padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 11px; cursor: pointer; font-family: var(--font-mono); }\n\n.ai-suggestions { text-align: center; padding: 20px 0; }\n.ai-hint { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 16px; }\n.suggest-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 8px; }\n.suggest-btn { padding: 12px; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);\n  border-radius: var(--radius); color: var(--text); font-family: var(--font-mono);\n  font-size: 12px; cursor: pointer; text-align: left; transition: all 0.15s; }\n.suggest-btn:hover { border-color: var(--gold-dim); color: var(--gold); }\n\n.ai-messages { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; padding: 8px 0; }\n.ai-msg { padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: var(--radius); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6;\n  max-width: 85%; word-wrap: break-word; }\n.ai-user { align-self: flex-end; background: var(--gold-bg); border: 1px solid var(--gold-dim); color: var(--text-bright); }\n.ai-assistant { align-self: flex-start; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); }\n.ai-error { color: var(--danger); font-size: 12px; }\n\n.typing-dots { display: flex; gap: 4px; padding: 4px 0; }\n.typing-dots span { width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--text-dim);\n  animation: blink 1.2s infinite; }\n.typing-dots span:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }\n.typing-dots span:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }\n@keyframes blink { 0%,100% { opacity:0.2; } 50% { opacity:1; } }\n\n.ai-input-row { display: flex; gap: 8px; padding-top: 12px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }\n.ai-input { flex: 1; padding: 12px; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border: 1px solid var(--border);\n  border-radius: var(--radius); color: var(--text); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; }\n.ai-send { padding: 12px 16px; background: var(--gold-bg); border: 1px solid var(--gold-dim);\n  color: var(--gold); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer; font-size: 16px; }\n```\n\n## More Tab (#tab-more)\n\n### Feature Card Grid\n```html\n<div class=\"more-grid\">\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('📖 Spells', buildSpellPanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">📖</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">Spells</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('🐉 Monsters', buildMonsterPanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">🐉</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">Monsters</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('👤 NPCs', buildNpcPanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">👤</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">NPCs</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('🗺️ Map', buildMapPanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">🗺️</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">Map</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('📝 Notes', buildNotesPanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">📝</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">Notes</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('📚 Guide', buildGuidePanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">📚</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">Guide</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('📜 History', buildHistoryPanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">📜</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">History</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"more-card\" onclick=\"openPanel('⚙️ Settings', buildSettingsPanel())\">\n    <span class=\"more-icon\">⚙️</span>\n    <span class=\"more-label\">Settings</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### More Card CSS\n```css\n.more-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 10px; }\n.more-card { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center;\n  gap: 8px; padding: 24px 16px; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);\n  border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s; }\n.more-card:hover { border-color: var(--gold-dim); background: var(--gold-bg); }\n.more-icon { font-size: 32px; }\n.more-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); }\n```\n\n### Panel Builder Functions\nCreate JS functions that return HTML strings for each panel. These use the `openPanel(title, html)` function from Agent 2.\n\n**Spells Panel:**\n```javascript\nfunction buildSpellPanel() {\n  return `<div class=\"panel-search\">\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"spell-search\" placeholder=\"Search spells...\" oninput=\"filterSpells()\" class=\"panel-input\">\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"spell-list\" class=\"panel-list\">Loading...</div>`;\n  // After render, fetch spells from /dnd-api/spells and render\n}\n// After openPanel, populate:\nsetTimeout(async () => {\n  const resp = await fetch('/dnd-api/spells');\n  const spells = await resp.json();\n  // Render spell cards\n}, 100);\n```\n\n**Guide Panel** — merge content from guide.html:\nRead ~/dnd-app/frontend/guide.html and extract the D&D guide content. Present it as collapsible accordion sections in the Guide panel.\n\n**Notes Panel** — use existing notes functionality:\n```javascript\nfunction buildNotesPanel() {\n  return `<textarea id=\"panel-notes\" class=\"notes-textarea\" placeholder=\"Session notes...\">${currentNotes || ''}</textarea>\n  <button class=\"save-btn\" onclick=\"saveNotes()\">Save Notes</button>`;\n}\n```\n\n**History Panel** — use existing session history:\n```javascript\nfunction buildHistoryPanel() {\n  return `<div id=\"history-list\" class=\"panel-list\">Loading...</div>`;\n  // Fetch from /dnd-api/sessions/history\n}\n```\n\n**Settings Panel:**\n```javascript\nfunction buildSettingsPanel() {\n  return `<div class=\"settings-list\">\n    <div class=\"setting-item\">\n      <span>Room PIN</span>\n      <span class=\"setting-value\">${currentPin || '—'}</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"setting-item\">\n      <span>Role</span>\n      <span class=\"setting-value\">${currentRole || '—'}</span>\n    </div>\n    <button class=\"action-btn danger\" onclick=\"endSession()\">End Session</button>\n    <button class=\"action-btn\" onclick=\"saveToObsidian()\">Save to Obsidian</button>\n  </div>`;\n}\n```\n\n## Rules\n- Read existing JS in index.html to find current function names and variables (currentPin, currentRole, currentNotes, etc.)\n- Reuse existing fetch patterns for spells/monsters/notes/history\n- AI chat calls `/dnd-api/rooms/:pin/ai-chat` (the Caddy route prefix is /dnd-api for DnD backend)\n- Actually check Caddy config for the correct API prefix — it might be different\n- Add all CSS inline in <style> blocks or append to styles.css\n- All touch targets minimum 48px\n- Font: JetBrains Mono everywhere, Cinzel for decorative headings only\n- Guide content: extract key sections from guide.html, present as accordion\n- Do NOT modify server.js (Agent 1 handles that)"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":4138,"cacheRead":342563,"cacheWrite":2978,"totalTokens":349680,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.10345,"cacheRead":0.1712815,"cacheWrite":0.0186125,"total":0.29334899999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775404854459}}
