{"type":"message","id":"5be3c823","parentId":"e800351f","timestamp":"2026-04-05T21:43:33.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n21:43 UTC = 05:43 WITA. Approaching quiet hours (23:00 WITA = 15:00 UTC... wait, that's wrong. WITA is UTC+8, so 21:43 UTC = 05:43 WITA next day — actually no. 21:43 UTC + 8 = 05:43 next day? No: 21:43 + 8 = 29:43 = 05:43 Apr 6. \n\nSo it's 05:43 WITA — early morning, within quiet hours (23:00-07:00). Lucy likely sleeping.\n\nWA gateway still flapping. Nothing new to alert about. Lucy's last message was about DEEP THINK feature — pending his response on \"build or deep think first.\"\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":198,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":373050,"totalTokens":373251,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.00495,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":2.3315625,"total":2.3365275}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775425400810}}
{"type":"message","id":"5fcdd902","parentId":"5be3c823","timestamp":"2026-04-06T02:30:15.992Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-06 02:24:55 UTC] WhatsApp gateway connected as +6281938953639.\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"AC7D2DD4336078FF08177189D80D3758\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+6285133221170\",\n  \"sender\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang (+6285133221170)\",\n  \"id\": \"+6285133221170\",\n  \"name\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang\",\n  \"e164\": \"+6285133221170\"\n}\n```\n\nsuruh Uriel books"}],"timestamp":1775442615922}}
{"type":"message","id":"f276057b","parentId":"5fcdd902","timestamp":"2026-04-06T02:31:22.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGue spawn Uriel buat langsung build:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_Sm77JsoB6hMub26cQc567L","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"uriel-deep-think-build","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":900,"task":"# Uriel — Build DEEP THINK + Visual Planner + 👼 Auto-Agent Button\n\nYou are Uriel, The Validator. Build these 3 features for MAGI v2.\n\n## Context\n- MAGI v2 backend: ~/magi-v2/backend/server.js (Fastify, port 3002)\n- MAGI v2 frontend: ~/magi-v2/frontend/ (vanilla HTML, shared CSS/JS in /shared/)\n- Already has: chat with WebSocket, roundtable (multi-agent), 12 AI agents via Bedrock\n- Backend uses BedrockRuntimeClient for AI calls\n\n## Read First\n- ~/magi-v2/backend/server.js (understand existing chat/roundtable patterns, Bedrock calls)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/chat/index.html (understand chat UI)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/roundtable/index.html (understand multi-agent discussion)\n- ~/magi-v2/frontend/shared/core.js (api() function)\n\n## Feature 1: DEEP THINK (Backend + Frontend)\n\nA 3-agent debate/brainstorm that produces a synthesized plan.\n\n### Backend: POST /api/deep-think\n\n```javascript\napp.post('/api/deep-think', async (req) => {\n  if (!requireAdmin(req)) return { ok: false, error: 'Admin required' }\n  const { topic, agents } = req.body || {}\n  if (!topic) return { ok: false, error: 'Topic required' }\n  \n  // Default 3 agents: Rafael (strategy), Uriel (technical), Samael (challenge)\n  const debateAgents = agents || ['rafael', 'uriel', 'samael']\n  \n  // Phase 1: Each agent gives initial take (parallel)\n  const initialResponses = await Promise.all(debateAgents.map(async (agentId) => {\n    const soul = AGENT_SOULS[agentId] || ''\n    const prompt = `${soul}\\n\\nYou are in a DEEP THINK debate session. Topic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nGive your initial analysis and position. Be specific, opinionated, and constructive. Consider risks, opportunities, and practical implementation. 300-500 words.`\n    const response = await callBedrock(prompt) // use existing Bedrock call pattern\n    return { agentId, phase: 'initial', response }\n  }))\n  \n  // Phase 2: Each agent responds to others' takes (sequential for context)\n  const debateResponses = await Promise.all(debateAgents.map(async (agentId) => {\n    const soul = AGENT_SOULS[agentId] || ''\n    const othersViews = initialResponses.filter(r => r.agentId !== agentId)\n      .map(r => `**${r.agentId}** said: ${r.response}`).join('\\n\\n')\n    const prompt = `${soul}\\n\\nDEEP THINK debate continues. Topic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nOther agents said:\\n${othersViews}\\n\\nRespond to their points. Where do you agree? Where do you push back? What did they miss? Be direct. 200-400 words.`\n    const response = await callBedrock(prompt)\n    return { agentId, phase: 'debate', response }\n  }))\n  \n  // Phase 3: Synthesis (use Rafael or a neutral agent)\n  const allContent = [...initialResponses, ...debateResponses]\n    .map(r => `**${r.agentId}** (${r.phase}): ${r.response}`).join('\\n\\n---\\n\\n')\n  const synthesisPrompt = `You are synthesizing a DEEP THINK debate session.\\n\\nTopic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nAll agent contributions:\\n${allContent}\\n\\nProduce a final synthesis:\\n1. **Consensus Points** — what everyone agrees on\\n2. **Key Debates** — where agents disagreed and the best resolution\\n3. **Recommended Plan** — concrete action items with priorities\\n4. **Risks & Mitigations** — top 3 risks identified\\n5. **Open Questions** — what still needs to be decided\\n\\nBe specific and actionable. This will be turned into a visual plan.`\n  const synthesis = await callBedrock(synthesisPrompt)\n  \n  // Save result\n  const result = {\n    id: 'dt-' + Date.now(),\n    topic,\n    agents: debateAgents,\n    phases: { initial: initialResponses, debate: debateResponses },\n    synthesis,\n    createdAt: Date.now()\n  }\n  \n  // Store in data/deep-thinks.json\n  const file = join(__dirname, 'data', 'deep-thinks.json')\n  let data = { items: [] }\n  try { data = JSON.parse(readFileSync(file, 'utf8')) } catch {}\n  data.items.unshift(result)\n  if (data.items.length > 20) data.items = data.items.slice(0, 20)\n  writeFileSync(file, JSON.stringify(data, null, 2))\n  \n  return { ok: true, result }\n})\n\n// List past deep thinks\napp.get('/api/deep-think', async (req) => {\n  const file = join(__dirname, 'data', 'deep-thinks.json')\n  try { return { ok: true, items: JSON.parse(readFileSync(file, 'utf8')).items } }\n  catch { return { ok: true, items: [] } }\n})\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Find the existing Bedrock call pattern in server.js. It likely uses `InvokeModelWithResponseStreamCommand` or similar. Create a helper `callBedrockSimple(prompt)` that returns a string response (non-streaming). Check how the existing roundtable or summary endpoints call Bedrock.\n\n### Frontend: New page ~/magi-v2/frontend/deep-think/index.html\n\nSimple page:\n- Import shared core.css, components.css, nav.js\n- Header: \"🧠 Deep Think\"\n- Input: Topic textarea + agent selector (checkboxes for 12 agents, default: Rafael, Uriel, Samael)\n- \"Start Deep Think\" button (admin only)\n- Progress: Show \"Phase 1: Initial analysis...\" → \"Phase 2: Debate...\" → \"Phase 3: Synthesis...\"\n- Result: Show each agent's initial take, then debate responses, then synthesis\n- Each agent response in a card with agent name/emoji\n- Synthesis section highlighted with special styling\n- \"Generate Visual Plan\" button (calls Feature 2)\n- Past deep thinks list at bottom\n\n## Feature 2: Visual Planner (auto-generated HTML page)\n\nAfter Deep Think completes, generate an interactive HTML visualization.\n\n### Backend: POST /api/deep-think/:id/visual\n\nTakes the deep-think result and generates a self-contained HTML page with:\n- Timeline of the debate\n- Decision tree / flow chart (CSS-based, not D3)\n- Risk matrix (color-coded grid)\n- Action items checklist\n- Agent positions compared\n\nSave the HTML to ~/magi-v2/frontend/diagrams/deep-think-{id}.html and return the URL.\n\nThe HTML generation can use a template string — no need for a complex generator. Just string interpolation with the deep-think data.\n\n## Feature 3: 👼 Auto-Agent Button\n\n### Backend: POST /api/suggest-agent\n\n```javascript\napp.post('/api/suggest-agent', async (req) => {\n  const { message, context } = req.body || {}\n  if (!message) return { ok: false, error: 'Message required' }\n  \n  const agentList = Object.entries(AGENTS).map(([id, a]) => \n    `${id}: ${a.name} — ${a.role || a.superpower || ''}`\n  ).join('\\n')\n  \n  const prompt = `Given this message and context, which agent should handle this? Pick the BEST one.\n\nAvailable agents:\n${agentList}\n\nUser message: \"${message}\"\n${context ? `Recent context: ${context}` : ''}\n\nReply with ONLY the agent ID (e.g., \"rafael\", \"uriel\", \"azrael\"). Nothing else.`\n  \n  const agentId = (await callBedrock(prompt)).trim().toLowerCase()\n  const agent = AGENTS[agentId]\n  \n  return { ok: true, agentId, agentName: agent?.name || agentId, reason: '' }\n})\n```\n\n### Frontend: Add 👼 button to Chat page\n\nIn ~/magi-v2/frontend/chat/index.html, add a button near the send button:\n```html\n<button class=\"angel-btn\" id=\"angelBtn\" onclick=\"suggestAgent()\" title=\"Auto-select best agent\">👼</button>\n```\n\nJS:\n```javascript\nasync function suggestAgent() {\n  const input = document.getElementById('chatInput');\n  const msg = input.value.trim();\n  if (!msg) { toast('Type a message first', 'info'); return; }\n  \n  const { data, error } = await api('suggest-agent', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    body: { message: msg }\n  });\n  if (error) { toast(error, 'error'); return; }\n  \n  // Auto-select the suggested agent\n  toast(`👼 Suggested: ${data.agentName}`, 'success');\n  // Set the agent in the UI (find the agent selector and update it)\n  selectAgent(data.agentId);\n}\n```\n\nStyle the 👼 button with gold glow on hover.\n\nAlso add to Roundtable page — same button but adds the suggested agent to the selected agents list.\n\n## Navigation\nAdd \"Deep Think\" to the nav sidebar in ~/magi-v2/frontend/shared/nav.js:\n- Add to CORE group: `{ id: 'deep-think', icon: '🧠', label: 'Deep Think', path: '/deep-think/' }`\n\n## Data Files to Create\n- ~/magi-v2/backend/data/deep-thinks.json → `{\"items\":[]}`\n\n## Rules\n- Read server.js FULLY to find existing Bedrock call patterns\n- Reuse existing BedrockRuntimeClient (do NOT create new one)\n- Follow existing code patterns\n- Create the deep-think frontend page from scratch\n- Add 👼 button to EXISTING chat page (targeted edit, don't rewrite)\n- Add 👼 button to EXISTING roundtable page (targeted edit)\n- Add nav entry\n- Restart PM2 after backend changes\n- Test all endpoints work"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":2744,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":375997,"totalTokens":378744,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.06860000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":2.34998125,"total":2.41859625}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775442615974}}
