{"type":"message","id":"fee0cd53","parentId":"e579f947","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:35:14.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue — the `api()` function from core.js might be timing out or the response is too large. Deep Think makes 7 Bedrock calls which takes 1-3 minutes. The default fetch timeout might kill it.\n\nAlso `data?.ok` — the backend returns `{ ok: true, result: {...} }` but `api()` returns `{ data, error }` where `data` IS the parsed response. So `data.ok` should be `true`. Let me check if `api()` checks response.ok:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_DmeZdfN6gestqnqt3KwZWl","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 20 \"export async function api\" ~/magi-v2/frontend/shared/core.js","timeout":5}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":216,"cacheRead":384878,"cacheWrite":427,"totalTokens":385522,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0054,"cacheRead":0.192439,"cacheWrite":0.00266875,"total":0.20051275}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775446505987}}
{"type":"message","id":"40f12c2c","parentId":"fee0cd53","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:35:14.284Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_DmeZdfN6gestqnqt3KwZWl","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"export async function api(path, options = {}) {\n  const token = getToken();\n  const url = path.startsWith('/') ? path : `/api/${path}`;\n  const headers = { ...options.headers };\n  if (token) headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${token}`;\n  if (options.body && typeof options.body === 'object' && !(options.body instanceof FormData)) {\n    headers['Content-Type'] = 'application/json';\n    options.body = JSON.stringify(options.body);\n  }\n  try {\n    const res = await fetch(url, { ...options, headers });\n    if (res.status === 401) { redirectLogin(); return { data: null, error: 'Unauthorized' }; }\n    const ct = res.headers.get('content-type') || '';\n    const data = ct.includes('json') ? await res.json() : await res.text();\n    if (!res.ok) {\n      const msg = typeof data === 'object' ? (data.error || data.message || 'Request failed') : data;\n      return { data: null, error: msg };\n    }\n    return { data, error: null };\n  } catch (err) {\n    toast(err.message || 'Network error', 'danger');"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":52,"aggregated":"export async function api(path, options = {}) {\n  const token = getToken();\n  const url = path.startsWith('/') ? path : `/api/${path}`;\n  const headers = { ...options.headers };\n  if (token) headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${token}`;\n  if (options.body && typeof options.body === 'object' && !(options.body instanceof FormData)) {\n    headers['Content-Type'] = 'application/json';\n    options.body = JSON.stringify(options.body);\n  }\n  try {\n    const res = await fetch(url, { ...options, headers });\n    if (res.status === 401) { redirectLogin(); return { data: null, error: 'Unauthorized' }; }\n    const ct = res.headers.get('content-type') || '';\n    const data = ct.includes('json') ? await res.json() : await res.text();\n    if (!res.ok) {\n      const msg = typeof data === 'object' ? (data.error || data.message || 'Request failed') : data;\n      return { data: null, error: msg };\n    }\n    return { data, error: null };\n  } catch (err) {\n    toast(err.message || 'Network error', 'danger');","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775446514245}}
